longBusinessSummary: Halmont Properties Corporation invests in real assets in Canada. The company invests in low-rise office, retail, residential, and industrial properties. It also invests in freehold timberlands and related manufacturing facilities. In addition, it provides financing and property advisory services to client companies. The company was formerly known as H.A.L. Concepts, Ltd. and changed its name to Halmont Properties Corporation in February 2007. Halmont Properties Corporation was incorporated in 2000 and is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.
